<h2>12. Outline of the Production Process</h2>

<p>Once an article has been accepted for publication, the manuscript files are sent into our production system. The
  article is copyedited by a professional copyeditor who will correspond directly with the author about needed
  revisions. An Editors' Summary of the study is also added. Once the article has been typeset, galley proofs are sent
  as PDFs to the author to check for serious errors of fact: errors in author names or affiliations, errors of
  scientific fact that would cause misunderstandings to readers, and printer's (introduced) errors. Other correction
  requests will not be fulfilled. Corrections to scientific errors may require editorial approval and cause delays. The
  prompt return of both the copyedited article and the proofs by authors will ensure that the article stays on deadline.
